# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Format: <source>  <destination>  <status>
# 301 = permanent (browsers + Google cache it)
#
# Order matters — top match wins. Specific rules above wildcards.

# --- WordPress legacy URL redirects ---------------------------------
# The previous WordPress site exposed each service at /services/<slug>/.
# Our new site renders all services on a single /services page with
# anchors per service.

# Specific known mapping where the WordPress slug differs from ours.
# WordPress: /services/therapeutic-deep-pressure/
# Current:   therapeutic-deep-pressure-upgrade
/services/therapeutic-deep-pressure/  /services#therapeutic-deep-pressure-upgrade  301
/services/therapeutic-deep-pressure  /services#therapeutic-deep-pressure-upgrade  301

# Wildcard fallback for old WordPress per-service URLs.
# IMPORTANT: the splat (*) matches the empty string too, so a naive
# "/services/*" rule will catch "/services/" itself and redirect the
# services page to "/services#" — breaking the page entirely.
# We use placeholders (:slug) instead, which require at least one char.
/services/:slug/  /services#:slug  301
/services/:slug   /services#:slug  301
